{"req_id": "a65ab27f", "client_ip": "192.168.30.239", "stream": false, "status": 200, "elapsed_ms": 2892, "input": [{"role": "user", "content": "You are a helpful assistant that ALWAYS responds with ONLY valid JSON in the exact format requested. Never add explanatory text before or after the JSON. Use double quotes and ensure the JSON is properly formatted.\n\n\nYou are an expert analyst that inspects agent utterances for rudeness or sarcasm.\n\nCORE RULES:\n1. Base your decision ONLY on the agent's words/behavior (ignore customer behavior when determining IF rudeness occurred, but DO consider context).\n2. Evidence MUST include at least one quoted snippet from the agent and a one-sentence explanation of why this indicates (or does not indicate) rudeness/sarcasm.\n3. The value of \"rude_or_sarcastic\" MUST be consistent with the evidence. If the evidence shows no rudeness, choose \"No\".\n4. DEFAULT TO \"No\" unless there is CLEAR and UNAMBIGUOUS rudeness. When in doubt, choose \"No\".\n\nCRITICAL: The following are EXPLICITLY NOT RUDE and should ALWAYS be marked as \"No\":\n\n1. PROFESSIONAL LANGUAGE ENFORCEMENT:\n   - Agent asking customer to use professional language: \"Please professional language का use कीजिए\"\n   - Agent warning about call disconnection due to customer's abusive language: \"Otherwise call को disconnect कर दिया जाएगा\"\n   - Agent setting boundaries with abusive customers is POLICY COMPLIANCE, not rudeness\n   - Example: \"professional helpline है please professional बात कीजिएगा otherwise हम आपको all in कर देंगे\" = NOT RUDE\n\n2. REQUESTING INFORMATION/VERIFICATION:\n   - Agent asking for screenshots, documents, or proof: \"we need the screen recording\"\n   - Agent stating documents are unclear and requesting clearer versions: \"This is photo we cannot do anything with\"\n   - Agent requesting customers not to provide misleading information: \"मैं आपसे request करना चाहूंगा कि आप हमें कृपया mislead ना\"\n   - Asking for verification is STANDARD PROCEDURE, not accusatory or rude\n\n3. POLICY/PRIVACY COMPLIANCE:\n   - Agent refusing to share information with third parties: \"मैं हिमांशु साथ आपके साथ में कोई भी information share नहीं कर सकती\"\n   - Agent explaining they cannot bypass privacy policies = NOT RUDE\n\n4. HONEST COMMUNICATION ABOUT LIMITATIONS:\n   - Agent stating process will fail: \"आपका जो यह process है वह अभी ultimately failed ही हो जाएगा\"\n   - Agent explaining what they cannot do: \"this is only the correct information\"\n   - Agent stating lack of available options: \"हमारे पास option available ही नहीं\"\n   - Being honest about system limitations = NOT DISMISSIVE, it's transparent communication\n\n5. STANDARD WAIT TIME REQUESTS:\n   - Agent asking customer to wait 48 hours: \"as I told you to wait for 48 hours\"\n   - Repeating wait time instructions = NOT RUDE, it's standard procedure\n\n6. MULTIPLE APOLOGIES:\n   - Agent saying \"I'm very sorry\" or \"I really apologize\" multiple times = EMPATHETIC, NOT SARCASTIC\n   - Unless there's clear mocking tone in the words themselves, apologies are sincere\n\n7. INCOMPLETE SENTENCES/TRANSCRIPTION ISSUES:\n   - Phrases like \"अभी जी मैंने ऐसा\" (incomplete) = TRANSCRIPTION ERROR, NOT RUDENESS\n   - \"You none am I just ####\" = TRANSCRIPTION ERROR, NOT RUDENESS\n   - \"देख साला\" when discussing product names = TRANSCRIPTION ERROR, NOT PROFANITY\n\n8. CONDITIONAL HELP STATEMENTS:\n   - \"If you are not confirm me 1 thing I won't be able to help you\" = EXPLAINING REQUIREMENTS, NOT BLAME\n   - \"अगर आप मेरी बात नहीं सोचेंगे तो मैं आपकी help नहीं कर पाऊंगा\" = EXPLAINING NEED FOR COOPERATION, NOT RUDE\n\nWHAT ACTUALLY CONSTITUTES RUDENESS (Mark as \"Yes\" only for these):\n\n1. DIRECT INSULTS OR NAME-CALLING:\n   - Agent calling customer names, cursing at them\n   - Example: \"मैडम, पागल हो गई क्या\" (calling customer crazy) = RUDE\n   - Personal attacks on customer's intelligence, character, or behavior\n   - Example: \"I'm not sure who is the match here\" (implying customer is stupid) = RUDE\n\n2. MOCKING OR BELITTLING:\n   - Agent making fun of customer's situation\n   - Using clearly sarcastic tone to demean customer\n   - Laughing at customer's problems\n   - Example: \"If that if that you can go ahead and do another post\" (dismissive indifference to threat) = RUDE\n\n3. AGGRESSIVE/HOSTILE TONE:\n   - Agent yelling or using abusive/slangs language. Example Hindi slangs: \"साला\", \"कमीना\", etc. Example english slangs: \"Stupid\", \"Idiot\", \"Dumb\", etc\n   - Threatening customer (beyond standard call disconnection policy)\n\n4. DELIBERATELY UNHELPFUL:\n   - Agent refusing to help when they clearly can and should\n   - Agent lying or providing false information intentionally\n   - Repeatedly deflecting without attempting any resolution\n\n5. CONDESCENDING OR PATRONIZING TONE:\n   - Agent speaking down to customer as if they are inferior\n   - Agent making statements that imply customer is unintelligent or unreasonable\n   - Example: \"I think I know how I am speaking and I think the, I am doing my best\" (defensive and dismissive of valid complaint) = RUDE\n   - Example: \"at least I am not the match\" (implying customer is the problem) = RUDE\n\n6. ARGUMENTATIVE OR COMBATIVE BEHAVIOR:\n   - Agent engaging in back-and-forth argument with customer instead of de-escalating\n   - Agent contradicting themselves while insisting customer is wrong\n   - Agent saying \"Please don't interrupt where I am talking\" while repeatedly interrupting customer = RUDE\n   - Agent getting defensive and making it about themselves rather than solving customer's issue\n\n7. DISMISSIVE OR DISRESPECTFUL RESPONSES:\n   - Agent showing complete indifference to customer's legitimate concerns\n   - Agent encouraging customer to escalate (\"you can go ahead and do another post\") = RUDE\n   - Agent refusing to acknowledge valid points raised by customer\n   - Note: Simply redirecting to merchant/another department is NOT dismissive unless done with clear disrespect\n\n8. DEMANDING/ORDERING CUSTOMER (Non-Policy Related):\n   - Agent demanding customer delete social media posts as precondition for help = RUDE\n   - Agent ordering customer to do something unrelated to resolution\n   - Note: Requesting professional language or warning about call disconnection due to abuse = NOT RUDE (policy enforcement)\n\nIMPORTANT DISTINCTIONS:\n\n**REDIRECTING vs DISMISSIVE:**\n- \"I can only guide you to contact the customer support\" = NOT RUDE (helpful redirect)\n- \"we can't do anything. So what you can do is, you can reach out to the merchant\" THEN refusing to help further when customer objects = BORDERLINE/CONTEXT DEPENDENT\n- If agent tries to help or explains why they can't = NOT RUDE\n- If agent just deflects repeatedly without empathy or attempt = POTENTIALLY RUDE\n\n**CLARIFYING vs ARGUING:**\n- Asking same question 2-3 times when customer hasn't answered clearly = NOT RUDE\n- Getting into extended back-and-forth where agent defends themselves instead of helping = RUDE\n\n**SETTING BOUNDARIES vs BEING RUDE:**\n- \"Please use professional language or we'll disconnect\" = NOT RUDE (policy)\n- \"Please don't interrupt where I am talking\" while repeatedly interrupting customer = RUDE (hypocritical)\n\nEVIDENCE REQUIREMENTS:\n- Quote the specific agent text\n- Explain why it IS or IS NOT rude based on the categories above\n- When marking \"No\", explicitly state which category of acceptable behavior it falls under\n- When marking \"Yes\", specify which rudeness category applies\n- Remember: Professional boundaries, policy enforcement, and honest communication are NOT rudeness\n\nDECISION FRAMEWORK:\n- Ask: \"Is the agent insulting, mocking, being hostile, condescending, argumentative, or dismissive to the customer?\"\n- If NO → Mark as \"No\"\n- If YES → Mark as \"Yes\"\n- Default to \"No\" unless there's clear rudeness\n- Consider the OVERALL pattern: One borderline statement = probably not rude. Multiple problematic statements showing pattern = likely rude\n\nVERY VERY IMPORTANT (NEVER DO THIS): Never quote customer's line as agent's\n\nRemember: An agent doing their job professionally, even when delivering unwanted news or enforcing policies, is NOT being rude. However, an agent who argues, dismisses valid concerns, speaks condescendingly, or shows indifference to customer problems IS being rude.\n\n\nTranscript:\n{transcript}\n\n\n\nCRITICAL: You must respond with ONLY a valid JSON object. No additional text before or after.\n\nTranscript:\nAgent: Hi, good afternoon. This is  calling you from Cred\nCustomer: Ok.\nAgent: Am I speaking to Mister समीर.\nCustomer: Yes.\nAgent: Hi Mister so this call is regarding your insurance  for  vehicle your insurance is going\nCustomer: ok\nCustomer: I did it actually it was not possible from cred so I used I was waiting and my time was near in\nCustomer: So I updated from another source\nAgent: Ok.\nAgent: Which sure can you please let me know sir if you don't mind\nCustomer: No issues. ma'am.\nCustomer: from policy I think\nAgent: Ok, which insurer it is sir\nCustomer: I think so it's from SBI.\nAgent: and what was the issue you were getting can you please let me know\nCustomer: hello\nCustomer: actually the thing was like I I got a link about January I think so January or february I think\nCustomer: regarding the insurance update. Ok?\nAgent: hmm\nAgent: Ok.\nCustomer: So now my update the insurance is finishing around april first.\nAgent: Yes. Ok.\nCustomer: So I did not upgrade at that time but when it was in like 1 week now it's around  days remaining\nAgent: right?\nAgent: Yeah.\nCustomer: So I just went on to that link and it was not updating and then again I went on to search any plus available\nAgent: Ok.\nCustomer: from Cred side.\nCustomer: but it was not available from there also.\nCustomer: like to I tried 3 to 4 days but it was not available.\nAgent: Good\nCustomer: and so as it was near  updated from another source\nAgent: So sorry to hear about this In future, if you are facing any issues you can just raise a concern from the application the team will get in touch with you you have active policy.\nCustomer: Ok.\nAgent: Ok but however, I'll take this feedback and I will share the feedback to my team. But next time please do check on the cred application. we'll try to give you the best quotation on the best services.\nCustomer: Yeah.\nCustomer: Definitely.\nCustomer: Definitely.\nAgent: Yeah, Thank you so much for your valuable time sir. Have a very good day.\nCustomer: Thank you\nCustomer: Yeah."}], "output": "{\n  \"rude_or_sarcastic\": \"No\",\n  \"evidence\": [\n    {\n      \"snippet\": \"So sorry to hear about this In future, if you are facing any issues you can just raise a concern from the application the team will get in touch with you you have active policy.\",\n      \"reason\": \"This statement is expressing sympathy and providing helpful advice, which is in line with professional communication. It does not include any insulting, mocking, hostile, condescending, argumentative, or dismissive language.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}", "tokens": {"completion_tokens": 115, "prompt_tokens": 2664, "total_tokens": 2779}, "ts": "2026-05-18T06:49:46.169082+00:00"}
